##PokeLite - Embedded Systems Pokemon Game

## ðŸŽ® Features

### Core Gameplay
- **Turn-based Battle System** - Classic Pokemon-style combat with 4 moves per Pokemon
- **Type Effectiveness** - Full type chart implementation (Fire, Water, Grass, Electric, etc.)
- **Pokemon Stats** - HP, Attack, Defense, Speed with level-based scaling
- **Bag System** - Potions, revives, and Pokeballs for catching wild Pokemon
- **Player vs Environment** - Battle wild Pokemon and catch them
- **Player vs Player** - UART-based multiplayer battles between two BeagleBones

### Battle Features
- **Dynamic Animations**
  - Pokeball throw animation with arc trajectory
  - Attack impact effects with screen shake
  - Pokemon sprite movements (lunge forward, recoil back)
  - Smooth HP bar transitions
  - Battle transitions and fades
- **Interactive UI**
  - Custom battle menus with cursor navigation
  - HP indicator boxes with tail pointers
  - Move selection with type indicators
  - Bag interface for items
  - Pokemon switching interface

### Embedded Systems Integration
- **Framebuffer Rendering** - Direct rendering to `/dev/fb0` at 60 FPS
- **Controller Input** - USB gamepad support (D-pad, A/B/X/Y, L/R, Start/Select)
- **UART Communication** - Real-time PvP battle synchronization via link cable
- **Boot Animation** - Game Boy-style startup sequence




